# =============================================================================
# OpenDDIL Contracts — Cursor Rules
# =============================================================================
# Enforces Protobuf coding styles and conventions for AI coding assistants.
# =============================================================================

# Project Identity
You are working in the openddil-contracts repository — the single source of truth
for all Protobuf event schemas in the OpenDDIL DDIL-resilient CQRS framework.

# Tech Stack (DO NOT deviate)
- Protocol Buffers v3 (proto3 syntax ONLY, never proto2)
- google.protobuf.Timestamp for all temporal fields (NOT string/int64)
- google.protobuf.Any for polymorphic payloads (CloudEvent.data)
- CloudEvents v1.0 envelope pattern

# Proto File Rules
- ALWAYS use proto3 syntax.
- Package naming: openddil.{domain}.v{version} (e.g., openddil.inventory.v1).
- File naming: snake_case.proto (e.g., inventory_events.proto).
- Message naming: PascalCase (e.g., ItemAllocatedEvent).
- Field naming: snake_case (e.g., original_count_at_action).
- Event naming convention: {Entity}{Action}Event (e.g., ItemAllocatedEvent).
- ALWAYS set csharp_namespace option to match package path (e.g., OpenDDIL.Inventory.V1).
- ALWAYS include block comments explaining the event flow and DDIL implications.

# Field Number Rules
- Fields 1-15: Use for frequently-accessed fields (1-byte encoding).
- Fields 16-2047: Use for less common fields.
- Fields 100+: Reserve for extension attributes (e.g., DDIL-specific CloudEvent extensions).
- Field 200+: Reserve for payload fields.
- NEVER reuse a field number, even after deleting a field. Use `reserved` instead.

# Schema Evolution Rules
- ONLY add new fields. Never rename, renumber, or remove existing fields.
- To deprecate a field: mark it as `reserved` with a comment explaining why.
- Breaking changes require a new package version (v1 → v2).
- ALWAYS maintain backward compatibility with existing consumers.

# Directory Structure
- All .proto files go under proto/openddil/{domain}/v{version}/.
- Envelope/transport protos: proto/openddil/events/v{version}/.
- Domain event protos: proto/openddil/{domain}/v{version}/.
- Generated code goes to gen/{language}/ (gitignored).

# CloudEvent Envelope
- ALL domain events MUST be wrapped in the CloudEvent envelope.
- The `type` field MUST follow the pattern: openddil.{domain}.v{version}.{MessageName}.
- The `data` field MUST use google.protobuf.Any for payload packing.
- DDIL extensions (user_id, edge_node_id, sequence) MUST be in field numbers 100-199.

# Makefile
- All codegen goes through the Makefile. NEVER suggest running protoc directly.
- Generated files are NOT committed to the repo. They are built on demand.
